==English==

===Etymology===
{{unk|en}}; perhaps from an African language (possibly {{der|en|yo|ófé|t=to evade, disappear}}).<ref>{{R:Online_Etymology_Dictionary|ofay}}</ref> Pig Latin for {{m|en|foe}}, though popularly posited, is probably not accurate.

A possible point of origin is Cab Calloway's ''Hepster's Dictionary'', where the word is defined as "Policeman or law enforcement, 'The Man'".

